Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=2020=20patch=200035=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20flush-path=20phase=20instrumentation?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add per-flip phase timing brackets and counters covering BOTH the slow
path (DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer) AND the fast path (the
SDL_DOSVesaDirect* helpers from patch 0034) so wave 20 Lever A can
identify what dominates the unmeasured ~11.6 ms misc slice on real
HW. Default-OFF, env-gated by SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR=1 (strict
"1" match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention).

Background — wave 18 + 19 closures:

The wave-18 measured per-flip flush is 16.7 ms. Wave 19 isolated the
pure dosmemput at ~4.0 ms (76800 bytes); wave 18's bypass measured
SDL dispatch glue at ~1.1 ms. That leaves ~11.6 ms unidentified —
the wave-20 Lever A target. Plausible candidates: palette DAC
programming on every flip, cursor compositing setup cost, surface
bookkeeping, format conversion, dosmemput pre/post DPMI thunk
overhead. Without instrumentation, prioritizing C/D/E is guessing;
per memory perf_predictions_unreliable.md, perf predictions on this
project have been 5-30× wrong. Diagnose before optimizing.

Dual-path coverage rationale:

The W20A iter run config is DV=1 + FORCE_LFB=1, which routes flips
through SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull (fast path), bypassing
DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer entirely. Slow-path-only
instrumentation would observe nothing. So this patch instruments
BOTH paths: slow-path stats fire when slow_path_uwfb_calls > 0 in
the block; fast-path stats fire when the corresponding direct-VESA
helper was called. The combined counter line confirms which path
actually dominated.

Mechanics:

- Hint cached on first call (-1 unknown / 0 / 1) so the hot path
  never getenv()s. When disabled, instrumentation collapses to a
  single int compare + a no-op timestamp store.

- Seven sample arrays (uint64 ns, 100 slots each, ~5.6 KB total):
  three slow-path (palette_dac, dosmemput, total) + four fast-path
  (present_full, program_palette, get_state, banked_flush).

- Eight counters per block: slow_path_uwfb_calls, palette_dac_calls,
  cursor_composite_calls, realloc_calls (lazy_reinit), and four
  direct_vesa_*_calls counters.

- block_events anchor: bumped by EITHER UWFB return (slow-path
  per-flip) OR SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull (fast-path per-flip).
  Sub-ops (GetState / ProgramPalette / BankedFlush direct call /
  4× internal ProgramVGADAC) bump their own counters but NOT the
  anchor. When block_events hits 100, _instr_emit_block fires.

- Helper functions: _instr_account_flip_and_maybe_emit (anchor
  bump + maybe emit), _instr_record_total_at_exit (slow-path
  return-recording), _instr_record_dv_phase (generic fast-path
  helper recording), _instr_record_dv_present_at_exit (PresentFull-
  specific recording that ALSO bumps the anchor).

- 4× ProgramVGADAC sites instrumented in UWFB (fast-path + 3
  normal-path); all four feed the slow-path palette_dac aggregator.
  ProgramVGADAC site inside SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette feeds
  the SEPARATE direct_vesa_program_palette aggregator so the
  operator can see which path called it.

- 1× dosmemput bracket on UWFB's fast-path VRAM-write block.
  Equivalent on the direct-VESA path is captured implicitly by
  present_full (which IS that block).

- 6× total brackets via _instr_record_total_at_exit covering all
  6 UWFB return paths (fast-path success, normal-path success, 4
  error returns).

- 4× direct-VESA function bodies instrumented end-to-end (every
  return path records, including early-error returns, so call
  counts reflect all entries).

- Cursor counter increments at the 2 normal-path cursor-visible
  blocks (banked + LFB sub-branches). Cave Story hides the system
  cursor at init, so expected baseline 0/100. Non-zero would
  indicate the engine isn't successfully suppressing the cursor.

- lazy_reinit counter increments when patch-0011's lazy-reinit
  branch fires (fb_state was invalidated and needs re-population).
  Reported as direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls in the combined counter
  line because non-zero on a direct-VESA run would signal the
  engine is hitting fall-back churn.

- Every 100 anchors _instr_emit_block qsorts each sample array,
  computes min/median/mean/p95/max, emits up to 7 stat lines + 1
  combined counter line + (rare) a banked_flush counter line, then
  resets all per-block state.

Output format:

  [uwfb-stat n=N phase=palette_dac     min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]   (slow-path only when called)
  [uwfb-stat n=N phase=dosmemput       ...]
  [uwfb-stat n=N phase=total           ...]
  [direct-vesa-stat n=N phase=present_full     ...]                                            (fast-path only when called)
  [direct-vesa-stat n=N phase=program_palette  ...]
  [direct-vesa-stat n=N phase=get_state        ...]
  [direct-vesa-stat n=N phase=banked_flush     ...]                                            (only if engine bypassed PresentFull)
  [flip-instr-counters slow_path_uwfb_calls=N palette_dac_calls=N cursor_composite_calls=N
                       direct_vesa_present_calls=N direct_vesa_palette_calls=N
                       direct_vesa_get_state_calls=N direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls=N
                       block_events=N]                                                         (always emitted)

palette_dac and program_palette stats both apply a low-N gate
(emit only when sample count ≥ 10) to avoid noisy single-sample
reports.

Coordination with engine side:

The companion engine patch (nxengine/0087) reads the same hint
SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR and emits its own [flip-stat …]
block over the same 100-flip window so a single env-var toggle
enables both layers' instrumentation simultaneously. Engine emits
its own brackets around the Renderer::flip() phases (drawcall
drain, dirty compute, present, housekeeping). docs/BOOT.md
edit lives in this patch by ownership convention; the engine
patch's commit message documents the hint's engine-side semantics
without duplicating the BOOT.md entry.

DOSKUTSU local patch (workspace-local; never upstreamed per project
sdl_ai_policy memory).
---
 include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h           |  75 ++++
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c | 536 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 611 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h b/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
index 9b05b3c45..8b3c610d2 100644
--- a/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
+++ b/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
@@ -1023,6 +1023,81 @@ extern "C" {
  */
 #define SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA"
 
+/**
+ * A variable that, when set to "1", enables per-flip phase timing brackets
+ * and counters inside the SDL3-DOS backend, covering BOTH the slow path
+ * (`DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer`) AND the fast path (the
+ * `SDL_DOSVesaDirect*` helpers from patch 0034), plus the engine-side
+ * `Renderer::flip()` brackets. Aggregates 100-flip min / median / mean /
+ * p95 / max statistics per phase to `sdldbg.log` (and the engine
+ * equivalent to `DEBUG.LOG`).
+ *
+ * **Default OFF.** Strict-match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention:
+ * only the literal string "1" activates (`e && e[0]=='1' && e[1]==0`).
+ *
+ * The instrumentation has its own per-flip cost (a handful of
+ * `SDL_GetTicksNS` calls plus an array store; ~tens of microseconds in
+ * total per flip). That cost is acceptable for a one-off diagnostic iter
+ * but biases any production fps measurement, which is why the default is
+ * OFF. Operators enable it for the wave-20 W20A iter only.
+ *
+ * Output format (every 100 flips, to `sdldbg.log`). Slow-path stats only
+ * fire when `slow_path_uwfb_calls > 0` in the block; fast-path stats
+ * only fire when the corresponding helper was called. The combined
+ * counter line is always emitted.
+ *
+ *     [uwfb-stat n=100 phase=palette_dac min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
+ *     [uwfb-stat n=100 phase=dosmemput   min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
+ *     [uwfb-stat n=100 phase=total       min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]
+ *     [direct-vesa-stat n=100 phase=present_full     ...]
+ *     [direct-vesa-stat n=N   phase=program_palette  ...]
+ *     [direct-vesa-stat n=100 phase=get_state        ...]
+ *     [direct-vesa-stat n=N   phase=banked_flush     ...]   (only if engine called BankedFlush directly)
+ *     [flip-instr-counters slow_path_uwfb_calls=N palette_dac_calls=N
+ *      cursor_composite_calls=N direct_vesa_present_calls=N
+ *      direct_vesa_palette_calls=N direct_vesa_get_state_calls=N
+ *      direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls=N block_events=N]
+ *
+ * Slow-path phases (only meaningful when `DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer`
+ * is called):
+ *  - `total` — function entry to exit; covers all sub-phases.
+ *  - `dosmemput` — narrow bracket around the VRAM-write block on the
+ *    fast path (LFB SDL_memcpy or banked dosmemput).
+ *  - `palette_dac` — narrow bracket around any of the 4 ProgramVGADAC
+ *    call sites (only fires when palette version changed; emitted only
+ *    when sample count ≥ 10 in the block to avoid noisy single-sample
+ *    reports).
+ *
+ * Fast-path phases (only meaningful when the engine takes the
+ * direct-VESA route via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA=1):
+ *  - `present_full` — full body of `SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull`; the
+ *    per-flip anchor on the fast path. In the wave-20 W20A run config
+ *    (DV=1 + FORCE_LFB=1) this is the dominant signal.
+ *  - `program_palette` — body of `SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette`;
+ *    same low-N gate as slow-path `palette_dac`.
+ *  - `get_state` — body of `SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState`; cheap
+ *    (struct-copy + a valid-flag check), but non-zero per call. Engine
+ *    typically calls once per flip if it re-snapshots on
+ *    generation-counter bumps.
+ *  - `banked_flush` — body of `SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush`; only
+ *    fires when the engine calls it directly for partial-flush. May
+ *    be zero in W20A.
+ *
+ * The hint is also consumed by the engine-side instrumentation in
+ * `Renderer::flip()` (NXEngine-evo / patches/nxengine-evo/0087) so a
+ * single env-var toggle enables both layers' instrumentation
+ * simultaneously. Background: wave 18 + 19 closed under measurement
+ * leaving ~11.6 ms of "misc" per flip unidentified between the measured
+ * 4.0 ms dosmemput and 1.1 ms SDL dispatch glue. Lever A is the
+ * diagnostic that identifies which phase dominates that misc slice;
+ * Levers C/D/E are right-sized based on its findings.
+ *
+ * Added by patches/SDL/0035 (DOSKUTSU local patch, never upstreamed).
+ * See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-20-COLD-PICKUP.md § 3 Lever A for the wave-20
+ * plan.
+ */
+#define SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR"
+
 /**
  * Set the level of checking for invalid parameters passed to SDL functions.
  *
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index 42e9ed907..1ee59c1e5 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -40,6 +40,7 @@
 #include <sys/movedata.h> // for dosmemput (banked framebuffer writes)
 #include <stdio.h>        // diagnostic file I/O (DOSKUTSU patches/SDL/0002)
 #include <unistd.h>       // fsync — crash-survive log writes on DOS (patch 0004)
+#include <stdlib.h>       // qsort — wave-20 flush instrumentation (patch 0035)
 
 // DOSKUTSU patch 0034 (Phase 9 wave 18) — direct-VESA generation counter.
 // Bumped whenever fb_state is invalidated (DOSVESA_InvalidateCachedFramebuffer)
@@ -49,6 +50,346 @@
 // needed; plain Uint32 is fine.
 static Uint32 _doskutsu_dvd_generation = 0;
 
+// ============================================================================
+// DOSKUTSU patch 0035 (Phase 9 wave 20) — flush-path instrumentation.
+//
+// Per-flip phase timing brackets + counters wrapped around
+// DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer to identify what dominates the
+// unmeasured ~11.6 ms "misc" slice on real HW (PODP83 + Cirrus +
+// UNIVBE). Every 100 flips we emit min / median / mean / p95 / max
+// per phase to sdldbg.log, then reset the sample arrays and counters.
+//
+// Default OFF; enabled by SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR=1 (strict "1"
+// match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention). The hint state is
+// cached on first call so the hot path doesn't getenv() per flip.
+//
+// The instrumentation has its own per-flip cost (a handful of
+// SDL_GetTicksNS calls + array stores; ~tens of us total). Acceptable
+// for the W20A diagnostic iter, but biases any production fps
+// measurement, which is why the default is OFF and operators are
+// expected to enable the hint only for the diagnostic run.
+//
+// Workspace-local; never upstreamed (per project sdl_ai_policy memory).
+// ============================================================================
+
+#define DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES 100  // flips per emit-and-reset block
+
+// Hint cache: -1 unknown, 0 disabled, 1 enabled. Sampled on first
+// DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer call.
+static int _instr_enabled_cached = -1;
+
+// Sample buffers (uint64 nanoseconds). Sized to DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES;
+// counters track how many slots are populated so we don't emit stats over
+// uninitialized entries (palette_dac in particular is sparsely populated —
+// the palette only changes once every 16-20 flips on the title screen).
+//
+// Slow-path buffers (DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer):
+static Uint64 _instr_pal_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_pal_n = 0;
+static Uint64 _instr_dos_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_dos_n = 0;
+static Uint64 _instr_tot_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_tot_n = 0;
+
+// Fast-path buffers (SDL_DOSVesaDirect* helpers, patch 0034). The W20A
+// run config (DIRECT_VESA=1 + FORCE_LFB=1) takes the fast path, so these
+// are the load-bearing buckets for the wave-20 misc-slice analysis.
+static Uint64 _instr_dv_present_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_dv_present_n = 0;
+static Uint64 _instr_dv_palette_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_dv_palette_n = 0;
+static Uint64 _instr_dv_get_state_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_dv_get_state_n = 0;
+static Uint64 _instr_dv_banked_flush_samples[DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES];
+static int    _instr_dv_banked_flush_n = 0;
+
+// Counters within the current 100-flip block (slow path):
+static Uint32 _instr_slow_path_uwfb_calls_block = 0; // entries into UWFB
+static Uint32 _instr_pal_calls_block            = 0; // 4 ProgramVGADAC sites
+static Uint32 _instr_cursor_calls_block         = 0; // normal-path cursor block
+static Uint32 _instr_realloc_calls_block        = 0; // populate_fb_state lazy-reinit
+
+// Counters within the current 100-flip block (fast path / direct-VESA):
+static Uint32 _instr_dv_present_calls_block      = 0;
+static Uint32 _instr_dv_palette_calls_block      = 0;
+static Uint32 _instr_dv_get_state_calls_block    = 0;
+static Uint32 _instr_dv_banked_flush_calls_block = 0;
+
+// Block-emit anchor: bumped by either UWFB's record_total_at_exit OR
+// SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull's per-call recording — whichever path
+// "owns" the per-flip flush. Sub-ops (GetState / ProgramPalette /
+// BankedFlush direct call / 4× internal ProgramVGADAC) bump their own
+// counters but do NOT bump this anchor; they're sub-operations within
+// a single flip and counting them would skew the block boundary.
+//
+// If the engine bypasses both UWFB and PresentFull (e.g., SDL_memcpy
+// through vram_ptr directly for the LFB path), the anchor never bumps
+// and the block never emits — that's correct: SDL-side has nothing
+// authoritative to report; engine-side instrumentation owns that case.
+static int _instr_block_events = 0;
+
+// Cumulative flip counter (across blocks) — for the "@flush=N" tag.
+static Uint32 _instr_total_flips = 0;
+
+// qsort comparator for Uint64 (ascending). Used by _instr_emit_block to
+// sort sample arrays before computing median/p95.
+static int _instr_cmp_u64(const void *a, const void *b)
+{
+    Uint64 x = *(const Uint64 *)a;
+    Uint64 y = *(const Uint64 *)b;
+    if (x < y) return -1;
+    if (x > y) return  1;
+    return 0;
+}
+
+// Format a nanosecond duration as "X.XX" milliseconds (two decimals)
+// into a caller-supplied 16-byte buffer. Returns the buffer for chaining
+// inside a single doskutsu_dbg_log call. Two decimals = 10 us granularity,
+// which is plenty for ms-scale phase timings.
+static const char *_instr_fmt_ms(Uint64 ns, char *buf16)
+{
+    // ns / 10000 = ms × 100; integer divide gives whole ms, modulo gives
+    // hundredths-of-ms. Cap the whole part at 99999 to fit "99999.99\0" in
+    // 16 bytes — sub-second phases never exceed this.
+    Uint64 ms_x100 = ns / 10000ULL;
+    Uint32 whole = (Uint32)(ms_x100 / 100ULL);
+    Uint32 frac  = (Uint32)(ms_x100 % 100ULL);
+    if (whole > 99999) whole = 99999;
+    SDL_snprintf(buf16, 16, "%lu.%02lu",
+                 (unsigned long)whole, (unsigned long)frac);
+    return buf16;
+}
+
+// Emit one phase's stat line to sdldbg.log over the current block's
+// samples. min/med/mean/p95/max computed over the populated portion of
+// `arr` (size `n`); arr is sorted in place. n must be >= 1 — caller
+// gates on this for the palette case.
+//
+// `tag` is the line-prefix tag — "uwfb-stat" for slow-path buckets,
+// "direct-vesa-stat" for fast-path buckets. Two tags lets the operator's
+// grep tooling separate the two layers cleanly while sharing a single
+// formatter.
+static void _instr_emit_phase(const char *tag, const char *phase,
+                              Uint64 *arr, int n,
+                              Uint32 cumulative_flips)
+{
+    if (n < 1) {
+        return;
+    }
+    // qsort populates arr ascending so arr[0]=min, arr[n-1]=max.
+    qsort(arr, (size_t)n, sizeof(Uint64), _instr_cmp_u64);
+
+    Uint64 sum = 0;
+    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
+        sum += arr[i];
+    }
+    Uint64 mean = sum / (Uint64)n;
+    Uint64 mn   = arr[0];
+    Uint64 mx   = arr[n - 1];
+    int idx_med = n / 2;                 // n=100 → 50; n=1 → 0 (the one)
+    int idx_p95 = (n * 95) / 100;
+    if (idx_p95 >= n) idx_p95 = n - 1;   // cover n=1..19 gracefully
+    Uint64 med = arr[idx_med];
+    Uint64 p95 = arr[idx_p95];
+
+    char b_min[16], b_med[16], b_mean[16], b_p95[16], b_max[16];
+    doskutsu_dbg_log(
+        "[%s n=%d phase=%s min=%s med=%s mean=%s p95=%s max=%s ms] @flush=%lu",
+        tag, n, phase,
+        _instr_fmt_ms(mn,   b_min),
+        _instr_fmt_ms(med,  b_med),
+        _instr_fmt_ms(mean, b_mean),
+        _instr_fmt_ms(p95,  b_p95),
+        _instr_fmt_ms(mx,   b_max),
+        (unsigned long)cumulative_flips);
+}
+
+// Emit + reset one block. Called when _instr_block_events reaches
+// DOSKUTSU_INSTR_BLOCK_SAMPLES (i.e., after 100 flip anchors fired —
+// either UWFB returns or SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull calls). Palette
+// stats suppressed below MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES (prevents noisy single-
+// sample reports — palette typically fires 5-10 times in a 100-flip
+// block, both on the slow path and on direct-VESA's program_palette).
+static void _instr_emit_block(void)
+{
+    const int MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES = 10;
+
+    // ---- Slow-path stats (DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer) ----
+    // In the W20A run config (DV=1 + FORCE_LFB=1), the slow path is
+    // expected to be silent (slow_path_uwfb_calls=0/100). When that's
+    // the case, the slow-path phase lines emit nothing (n=0 → early
+    // return inside _instr_emit_phase) — only the counters line below
+    // confirms the slow path was bypassed. If something forces the
+    // slow path mid-run (lazy-reinit fall-back, mode change), these
+    // lines start populating and reveal the regression.
+    if (_instr_pal_n >= MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES) {
+        _instr_emit_phase("uwfb-stat", "palette_dac",
+                          _instr_pal_samples, _instr_pal_n,
+                          _instr_total_flips);
+    } else if (_instr_pal_n > 0) {
+        doskutsu_dbg_log(
+            "[uwfb-stat n=%d phase=palette_dac low_sample_count "
+            "(below MIN=%d, stats omitted)] @flush=%lu",
+            _instr_pal_n, MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES,
+            (unsigned long)_instr_total_flips);
+    }
+    _instr_emit_phase("uwfb-stat", "dosmemput",
+                      _instr_dos_samples, _instr_dos_n,
+                      _instr_total_flips);
+    _instr_emit_phase("uwfb-stat", "total",
+                      _instr_tot_samples, _instr_tot_n,
+                      _instr_total_flips);
+
+    // ---- Fast-path stats (SDL_DOSVesaDirect* helpers) ----
+    // present_full is the per-flip anchor; in the W20A run it should
+    // be the dominant signal. program_palette is sparse (palette
+    // version-bumps); apply the same low-N gate as the slow-path
+    // palette_dac. get_state fires per flip if engine re-snapshots;
+    // banked_flush only if engine bypasses PresentFull for partial-
+    // flush (expected zero in W20A).
+    _instr_emit_phase("direct-vesa-stat", "present_full",
+                      _instr_dv_present_samples, _instr_dv_present_n,
+                      _instr_total_flips);
+    if (_instr_dv_palette_n >= MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES) {
+        _instr_emit_phase("direct-vesa-stat", "program_palette",
+                          _instr_dv_palette_samples, _instr_dv_palette_n,
+                          _instr_total_flips);
+    } else if (_instr_dv_palette_n > 0) {
+        doskutsu_dbg_log(
+            "[direct-vesa-stat n=%d phase=program_palette low_sample_count "
+            "(below MIN=%d, stats omitted)] @flush=%lu",
+            _instr_dv_palette_n, MIN_PALETTE_SAMPLES,
+            (unsigned long)_instr_total_flips);
+    }
+    _instr_emit_phase("direct-vesa-stat", "get_state",
+                      _instr_dv_get_state_samples, _instr_dv_get_state_n,
+                      _instr_total_flips);
+    _instr_emit_phase("direct-vesa-stat", "banked_flush",
+                      _instr_dv_banked_flush_samples,
+                      _instr_dv_banked_flush_n,
+                      _instr_total_flips);
+
+    // ---- Combined counter line (one place for both paths) ----
+    // direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls reuses the same observable as the
+    // slow-path lazy-reinit counter (populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb
+    // recovery fires) — non-zero on a direct-VESA run signals SDL is
+    // re-populating fb_state mid-run, which the engine handles by
+    // re-snapshotting on generation bump (see patch 0034 doc-comments).
+    doskutsu_dbg_log(
+        "[flip-instr-counters slow_path_uwfb_calls=%lu "
+        "palette_dac_calls=%lu cursor_composite_calls=%lu "
+        "direct_vesa_present_calls=%lu direct_vesa_palette_calls=%lu "
+        "direct_vesa_get_state_calls=%lu direct_vesa_lazy_reinit_calls=%lu "
+        "block_events=%d] @flush=%lu",
